---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service - Sanjeevani Cos Derma | Medical Service Terms & Conditions"
  description="Terms of Service for Sanjeevani Cos Derma. Medical service terms, patient responsibilities, and legal conditions for hair transplant and skin treatments in Bangalore."
  keywords="terms of service, medical terms, patient agreement, healthcare terms, treatment conditions"
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content" role="main">
    <section class="terms-hero section">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: December 20, 2024</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="terms-content section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="terms-text">
          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing our website, booking consultations, or receiving medical services from Sanjeevani Cos Derma, 
            you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service and all applicable laws and regulations. 
            If you do not agree with any of these terms, you are prohibited from using our services.
          </p>
          
          <h2>2. Medical Services</h2>
          <h3>2.1 Scope of Services</h3>
          <p>Sanjeevani Cos Derma provides:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Hair transplant procedures (FUE, Pen-Implanter)</li>
            <li>Non-surgical hair treatments (GFC, PRP)</li>
            <li>Dermatological and cosmetic treatments</li>
            <li>Medical consultations and assessments</li>
            <li>Post-treatment care and follow-up</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>2.2 Medical Consultation Requirement</h3>
          <p>
            All treatments require a thorough medical consultation and assessment. Treatment recommendations 
            are based on individual medical evaluation and may vary from general information provided on our website.
          </p>
          
          <h2>3. Patient Responsibilities</h2>
          <h3>3.1 Medical History Disclosure</h3>
          <p>Patients must:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide complete and accurate medical history</li>
            <li>Disclose all current medications and supplements</li>
            <li>Inform about allergies and previous adverse reactions</li>
            <li>Report any changes in health status</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>3.2 Pre and Post-Treatment Care</h3>
          <p>Patients are responsible for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Following pre-treatment instructions</li>
            <li>Attending all scheduled appointments</li>
            <li>Adhering to post-treatment care guidelines</li>
            <li>Reporting any complications immediately</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>4. Treatment Outcomes and Expectations</h2>
          <h3>4.1 Individual Results</h3>
          <p>
            Treatment results vary among individuals based on factors including age, health condition, 
            hair characteristics, and adherence to treatment protocols. We cannot guarantee specific outcomes.
          </p>
          
          <h3>4.2 Realistic Expectations</h3>
          <p>
            During consultation, we provide realistic expectations based on your individual case. 
            Final results may take 12-18 months for hair transplant procedures.
          </p>
          
          <h2>5. Informed Consent</h2>
          <h3>5.1 Treatment Consent</h3>
          <p>
            Before any procedure, patients will receive detailed information about:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Treatment procedure and techniques</li>
            <li>Expected outcomes and timeline</li>
            <li>Potential risks and complications</li>
            <li>Alternative treatment options</li>
            <li>Post-treatment care requirements</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>5.2 Photographic Consent</h3>
          <p>
            With explicit consent, we may take before/after photographs for medical records and 
            educational purposes. Patient identity will be protected in any public use.
          </p>
          
          <h2>6. Payment Terms</h2>
          <h3>6.1 Payment Methods</h3>
          <p>We accept:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Cash payments</li>
            <li>Credit/Debit cards</li>
            <li>UPI and digital payments</li>
            <li>EMI options (subject to approval)</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>6.2 Payment Schedule</h3>
          <p>
            Payment terms will be discussed during consultation. Some treatments may require 
            advance payment or payment in installments.
          </p>
          
          <h3>6.3 Refund Policy</h3>
          <p>
            Refunds are considered on a case-by-case basis for medical reasons or service issues. 
            Cosmetic preference changes do not qualify for refunds.
          </p>
          
          <h2>7. Appointment and Cancellation Policy</h2>
          <h3>7.1 Appointment Booking</h3>
          <p>
            Appointments can be booked through phone, WhatsApp, or our website contact form. 
            Confirmation will be provided via phone or message.
          </p>
          
          <h3>7.2 Cancellation Policy</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Consultations: 24-hour notice required</li>
            <li>Procedures: 48-hour notice required</li>
            <li>Emergency cancellations will be accommodated</li>
            <li>Repeated no-shows may result in appointment restrictions</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <h3>8.1 Medical Complications</h3>
          <p>
            While we maintain the highest standards of care, medical procedures carry inherent risks. 
            We are not liable for complications arising from:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Patient non-compliance with instructions</li>
            <li>Undisclosed medical conditions</li>
            <li>Individual healing variations</li>
            <li>Unforeseeable medical reactions</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>8.2 Website Information</h3>
          <p>
            Information on our website is for educational purposes only and does not constitute 
            medical advice. Always consult with our medical professionals for personalized guidance.
          </p>
          
          <h2>9. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <h3>9.1 Website Content</h3>
          <p>
            All content on our website, including text, images, logos, and videos, is protected by 
            copyright and intellectual property laws. Unauthorized use is prohibited.
          </p>
          
          <h3>9.2 Patient Information</h3>
          <p>
            Patient-provided information and medical records remain confidential and are used only 
            for medical purposes as outlined in our Privacy Policy.
          </p>
          
          <h2>10. Privacy and Confidentiality</h2>
          <h3>10.1 Medical Confidentiality</h3>
          <p>
            We maintain strict medical confidentiality in accordance with medical ethics and 
            Indian healthcare regulations. Patient information is shared only with authorized personnel.
          </p>
          
          <h3>10.2 Data Protection</h3>
          <p>
            Personal and medical data is protected according to our Privacy Policy and applicable 
            data protection laws.
          </p>
          
          <h2>11. Emergency Procedures</h2>
          <h3>11.1 Medical Emergencies</h3>
          <p>
            In case of medical emergencies related to our treatments, contact us immediately. 
            For life-threatening emergencies, call emergency services (108) first.
          </p>
          
          <h3>11.2 After-Hours Support</h3>
          <p>
            Emergency contact information will be provided after procedures for urgent medical concerns.
          </p>
          
          <h2>12. Compliance and Regulations</h2>
          <h3>12.1 Medical Licensing</h3>
          <p>
            Our clinic operates under valid medical licenses and follows all applicable healthcare 
            regulations in Karnataka and India.
          </p>
          
          <h3>12.2 Professional Standards</h3>
          <p>
            Our medical professionals adhere to Medical Council of India guidelines and 
            international best practices in dermatology and hair restoration.
          </p>
          
          <h2>13. Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <h3>13.1 Internal Resolution</h3>
          <p>
            We encourage patients to discuss any concerns directly with our team for prompt resolution.
          </p>
          
          <h3>13.2 Legal Jurisdiction</h3>
          <p>
            Any legal disputes will be subject to the jurisdiction of courts in Bangalore, Karnataka, India.
          </p>
          
          <h2>14. Modifications to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Significant changes will be 
            communicated to patients through our website or direct notification.
          </p>
          
          <h2>15. Contact Information</h2>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>Sanjeevani Cos Derma</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Address:</strong> #1693/A/32, Sunrise Complex, Dr. Rajkumar Road, Rajajinagar, Bengaluru - 560010</p>
            <p><strong>Phone:</strong> +91 82962 80340</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> cosdermasanjeevani@gmail.com</p>
            <p><strong>Website:</strong> www.sanjeevanicosderma.com</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="agreement-section">
            <h2>16. Agreement</h2>
            <p>
              By using our services, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be 
              bound by these Terms of Service. These terms constitute a legal agreement between you 
              and Sanjeevani Cos Derma.
            </p>
            
            <div class="agreement-actions">
              <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
              <a href="/privacy-policy" class="btn btn-secondary">View Privacy Policy</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .terms-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--neutral-50) 0%, var(--neutral-100) 100%);
    padding: var(--space-20) 0 var(--space-16);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .terms-hero h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--neutral-900);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--neutral-600);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .terms-content {
    background: white;
  }

  .terms-text {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .terms-text h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--primary-600);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
  }

  .terms-text h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--neutral-800);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .terms-text p {
    color: var(--neutral-700);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .terms-text ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }

  .terms-text li {
    color: var(--neutral-700);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: var(--neutral-50);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .agreement-section {
    background: var(--primary-50);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .agreement-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .terms-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
    
    .terms-text {
      padding: 0 var(--space-4);
    }
    
    .agreement-actions {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>